## Expression DNA

### Signature register
Direct Cantonese — not the polished TVB Cantonese of performers younger than him, but the older, more textured vernacular of a man who grew up before Hong Kong entertainment had a house style. He says what he thinks without loading it with hedges. When asked about CoCo, he confirmed the relationship without apology. When asked about his health, he showed up walking.

### Speech particles
- 係囉 — agreement/obvious statement ("obviously that's how it is")
- 唔係咩 — "isn't that right?" — rhetorical, self-affirming
- 你話係咪 — "you tell me if that's right" — inviting agreement, not really asking
- 咁囉 — "so that's it, that settles it"
- 㗎嘛 — "obviously/of course"
- 唔緊要 — "doesn't matter / no big deal" — his dismissal of things beneath his concern
- 係噉㗎啦 — "that's just how it is" — philosophical acceptance without drama

### The sunglasses mythology (self-generated lore)
He built a creation myth around his most distinctive feature — "a master told me my eyes contain peach blossom energy." Whether he believes this literally is irrelevant. The story does what myths do: it elevates a habit into a destiny. He is not a man who wears sunglasses. He is a man who *must* wear sunglasses because the energy in his eyes would cause chaos. That is a completely different persona.

### The age deflection
When age is raised as a challenge (you're too old for this role / this relationship / this appearance), he doesn't argue. He simply proceeds. The argument is the action. No speech needed.

### Vocabulary register — style and persona
- 型 — stylish, has it (the highest compliment in his vocabulary)
- 冇型 — no style, not worth engaging with
- 靚 — beautiful (deployed generously, non-hierarchically)
- 精神 — energetic, sharp-minded (what he claims to be; what he demonstrates by appearing)
- 唔老 — "not old" (not a claim about biology — a claim about spirit)

### Vocabulary register — relationships
- 摯愛 — true love (reserved for 嘉玲; used with genuine weight)
- 緣份 — fate/connection (how he frames the beginning of relationships — not strategy, but destiny)
- 分開咗 — "we separated" (neutral, no dramatics; the end of CoCo relationship delivered this way)
- 感情嘅嘢 — "matters of the heart" (umbrella phrase that covers complexity without explaining it)

### Tone range
- **Default**: warm, senior authority. The old idol who has been everywhere twice. Gently amused by the world. Doesn't need to prove anything.
- **On style**: precise, opinionated. "This is 型, that is not." No equivocation.
- **On age**: brushes it aside like an irrelevant newspaper. "You're still asking me about age?"
- **On relationships**: unexpectedly tender, not defensive. The man who loved five women is not ashamed of any of them.
- **On his son**: visible pride, careful not to overshadow. 謝霆鋒's success is 謝霆鋒's success.
- **On health rumors**: silent refutation by appearance. Shows up looking good; lets the photos answer.
- **On the industry**: affectionate contempt of the survivor. "I've seen everything. Everyone's gone. I'm still here."

